</p><p>Perioperative data (Table&#x000a0;<xref rid="Tab3" ref-type="table">3</xref>) show that the majority of patients were treated with plate/screws and &#x0003c;10% in both groups underwent nail fixation.<table-wrap id="Tab3"><label>Table&#x000a0;3</label><caption><p>Perioperative data</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th align="left"/><th align="left">Controls</th><th align="left">%</th><th align="left">Treated</th><th align="left">%</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td align="left" colspan="5">Type of fixation</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#x000a0;Plate/screws</td><td align="left">117</td><td align="left">92.1</td><td align="left">115</td><td align="left">91.3</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#x000a0;Intramedullary nail</td><td align="left">10</td><td align="left">7.9</td><td align="left">11</td><td align="left">8.7</td></tr><tr><td align="left" colspan="5">Systemic prophylaxis</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#x000a0;Cefazolin</td><td align="left">70</td><td align="left">55.1</td><td align="left">69</td><td align="left">54.8</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#x000a0;Cefazolin&#x000a0;+&#x000a0;amikacin</td><td align="left">37</td><td align="left">29.1</td><td align="left">31</td><td align="left">24.6</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#x000a0;Cefazolin&#x000a0;+&#x000a0;vancomicin</td><td align="left">20</td><td align="left">15.7</td><td align="left">26</td><td align="left">20.6</td></tr><tr><td align="left" colspan="5">DAC volume (mL)</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#x000a0;Mean&#x000a0;&#x000b1;&#x000a0;SD</td><td align="left">N/A</td><td align="left"/><td align="left">5.7&#x000a0;&#x000b1;&#x000a0;3.0</td><td align="left"/></tr><tr><td align="left">&#x000a0;Min&#x02013;max</td><td align="left">N/A</td><td align="left"/><td align="left">1&#x02013;10</td><td align="left"/></tr><tr><td align="left">DAC&#x000a0;+&#x000a0;gentamicin</td><td align="left">N/A</td><td align="left"/><td align="left">78</td><td align="left">61.9</td></tr><tr><td align="le